Company News




Jun. 28, 2017 Samuel A. Ramirez Sr. is presented with the 2017 Maynard Jackson Award
NASP
The National Association of Securities Professionals is proud to present the 2017 Maynard Jackson Entrepreneur of the Year Award to Samuel A. Ramirez Sr., the President and CEO of Ramirez & Co.




Jun. 06, 2017 Ramirez & Co. hires Marty Teevan to bolster fixed income trading
S&P Global
Ramirez & Co. has hired seasoned industry veteran Marty Teevan as the firm continues to
bolster its taxable fixed income sales and trading group. Teevan will focus on high-yield, distressed, and special situations as a senior salesperson.




May. 17, 2017 Samuel A. Ramirez & Co., Inc Assigned AA- Rating
Press Release
"The strong credit rating speaks volumes about the longevity and strength of our company, the quality of our management, our diverse businesses and solid financial profile," said Samuel A. Ramirez Sr., President and CEO of Ramirez & Co.




May. 16, 2017 Bond Math Tells One Analyst That Ultra-Long Treasuries Would Save the U.S. Money
Bloomberg
"A basic exercise in bond math shows that the government would likely save money by stretching its yield curve to the 50-year mark." -Niso Abuaf, Head of the financial strategy group at Ramirez & Co.






